cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper deals with image recognition, specifically landmark recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a deep neural network and metric learning also suggests that it could fall under the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of defining landmarks and the need for a database, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of the system in a production environment, which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
